<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 4:54PM MDT  by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Morgan
and north central Adams Counties through 530 PM MDT...
At 454 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles southeast of Prospect Valley, or 34 miles southwest of Fort
Morgan, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hoyt.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
northeastern Colorado.</instruction>
